    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>City of Lafayette adjoining New Orleans La.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><date>November 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1849</date> corresponding
                with the <date>23<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> day of<lb/>Heshvan 5610</date>.</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqre.</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Editor of the Occident.—</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.—</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">The Israelites of this place have added one<lb/> more place of
                worship dedicated to the Supreme Ruler of the Universe; —“The<lb/> Great and holy
                One of <persName>Jacob</persName>.”—Under the name and style of <hi rend="underline"
                    >Dover tof</hi>.<lb/> It is to be hoped that our march is onward; —Although our
                number here is<lb/> at present but small we have a <sic>fare</sic> prospect of
                increase. We have <sic>temporar„<lb/>„ ry</sic> only rented a house for a place of
                worship, and number about forty families<lb/> who were previous compelled to attend
                the Synagogue in <placeName>New Orleans</placeName> a<lb/> distance of about two
                miles from the Centre of <placeName>Lafayette</placeName>.—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I hope soon to be able to give a better account of ourselves,
                as<lb/> we are about to make a move among our brethren Israelites, to collect<lb/>
                sufficient funds to purchase a lot of Ground and build a Synagogue.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">At a meeting held last <date>Sunday November 4th 1849</date>. The
                following<lb/> officers were duly elected to serve for the balance of the year
                    <date>5610</date>. viz<lb/>
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Young</persName> President <persName>Jacob
                    Meyer</persName> Vice President <persName>H. Asher</persName>,<lb/>
                <persName>Benjm. Goldenberg</persName> and <persName>B. Frank</persName>, Trustees,
                    <persName>N. Grunsburger</persName> Treasurer, and <persName>Julius
                    Layn</persName> Secretary—we have adopted German <hi rend="underline"
                    >minnic</hi>.—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The above information is respectfully submitted for the use of
                your<lb/> valuable monthly periodical by</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Your obt. &amp; Humble Servant.</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Young</persName>
            </p>
